The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic in a sample of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\).

For a continuous distribution, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\). This probability is equivalent to the probability that at least seven of the eight observations are less than or equal to 27.3. Given that \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\), the cumulative distribution function \(F(27.3) = 0.7\), so the probability that an individual observation is less than or equal to 27.3 is 0.7.

Let \(X\) be the number of observations less than or equal to 27.3. Then \(X\) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\). The required probability is \(P(X \geq 7) = P(X = 7) + P(X = 8)\).

