- \(P(X = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8\)

Compute the powers of 0.7:
- \((0.7)^7 = 0.0823543\)
- \((0.7)^8 = 0.05764801\)

Then:
- \(P(X = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032\)
- \(P(X = 8) = 0.05764801\)

Sum the probabilities:
- \(P(X \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833\)

