The probability that both balls drawn are the same color is given as \( \frac{151}{300} \). Let \( r \) be the number of red balls in the second urn. The first urn has 8 red and 7 blue balls, so the total number of balls in the first urn is 15. The second urn has \( r \) red balls and 9 blue balls, so the total is \( r + 9 \).

The probability of drawing two red balls is \( \frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r+9} \).  
The probability of drawing two blue balls is \( \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r+9} \).  
The probability of the same color is the sum:  
\[
\frac{8}{15} \times \frac{r}{r+9} + \frac{7}{15} \times \frac{9}{r+9} = \frac{8r + 63}{15(r+9)}
\]  
