For the single bonds:  
- Typical length = 1.53 Å  
- Benzene length = 1.397 Å  
- \( \Delta x = 1.397 - 1.53 = -0.133 \) Å (compression, magnitude 0.133 Å)  
- Force constant \( k = 500 \, \text{N/m} \)  
- Energy per single bond = \( \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times (0.133)^2 = 4.42225 \times 10^{-20} \, \text{J} \)  
